name: Snowshoe trek to Cima del Lago

route.description: This short and easy excursion winds its way along the right bank of the Venegia valley, in the presence of the Pale di San Martino Dolomites, and offers a truly spectacular panorama.moderate  6.4km3:30 h592m591m The Val Venegia is rightly known as one of the most beautiful valleys in the Dolomites. The panorama from Malga Ritorto is exceptional as you look out over the Brenta Dolomites mountain range. The view is especially stunning at dusk, when the setting sun colors the rocky spires pink. route.description: An uphill itinerary from Sant’Antonio di Mavignola to Clemp, where there is an extraordinary vista point overlooking the Rendena Valley, the Brenta Dolomites, and the Adamello mountain range.moderate  2.5km1:29 h382m0m An excursion of intermediate difficulty that winds up steeply through the woods to Clemp, which overlooks the valley below and out across the Adamello mountain range to the west and the Brenta Dolomites to the east, both of which form the Rendena Valley in the middle. Because of its strategic position, the area of Clemp was selected for the construction of an ancient fortress that was used as an Austrian outpost during World War I. The remains of this structure are visitable to this day. The area also features several characteristic mountain huts known locally as “case da mont”.Author’s recommendationBe sure to bring a camera. name: Anello del Monte Maggio - Passo Coe

route.description: A not too difficult informative circular tour, which offers extensive views of the Altopiano di Folgaria and much more: from the peak of Monte Maggio views sweep from the Pasubio to the Brenta Dolomites and the Lagorai mountain range.moderate  7.1km3:30 h334m335m The Passo Coe area is an ideal ground for snowshoeing: a broad plateau with magnificent woods alternates with sunny pastures, where most of the peaks can be reached without too much difficulty. The only drawbacks are the newly created ski trails towards Costa d'Agra, which have effectively stopped tours in the northern area. Luckily, further south, towards the slopes of Monte Maggio, you can still find quieter areas appreciated by those who more discreetly move among nature... To illustrate the most interesting aspects of the area, we have involved our colleague Mario Martinelli, who is very familiar with these places that he has known for a lifetime. Together we have followed a great circular route, chancing upon animal tracks, “out-of-season” flowers, artefacts from the war and much more... An example of how, also in winter, the mountains covered at a walking pace offer a multitude of surprises and stories to tell. Such treasures make us think that, perhaps, it should be given greater consideration by those who are involved in developing tourism in the local area.Author’s recommendation4LAND n.119 “Folgaria-Altipiani” map (1:25.000)     Author VisitTrentinoUpdated: September 23, 2020  The Passo Coe area is an ideal ground for snowshoeing: a broad plateau with magnificent woods alternates with sunny pastures, where most of the peaks can be reached without too much difficulty. Views: Great views to the Latemartowers, a wonderful view to the Rosengarten and Schlern. Fascinating: famous rock buildings, legends of the Latemar and the lake of Carezza 13.3km4:48 h439m413m Transfer by bus to the Karerpass, 1740m. The hiking tour starts here and leads between forest and over the Latemar meadows up to the entrance into the small “Latemarscharte”. Here you are directly under the steep Latemar towers, approx. on 2000m. After a descent of 100 meters you will enter the "Labyrinth": an enormous rock break. Here the path leads us through the stones up and down finally to arrive on the timber line. At the end of the rock labyrinth the path descends to the “Mitterleger”, 1820m, a beautiful larch clearing with a forest hut and a spring. The way back leads you between the wonderful forest over the sea of Carezza. It goes further along the cross country ski route passing the hotel Moseralm on the sunny side of the Karerpass and on an easy ascent up to the Jolanda hut. From here you return by ski bus back to the Cyprianerhof.     Author Cyprianerhof Dolomit ResortUpdated: May 05, 2019  Transfer by bus to the Karerpass, 1740m.
